I had the lobster ramen without the spiciness lol. The tail and claw had a good enough amount of meat, east to get to. Tasted pretty darn good too. The broth of the ramen was very flavorful. I wish there were more noodles, but alas the lobster is the star of the dish. The ramen bowl as a whole was fulfilling and I think the $28 is worth it. Awesomely delicious 😋

This used to be my favorite Ramen spot in the neighborhood. I called the store directly not wanting for Seamless to get a chunk of their profits and placed my pickup order. I went with my to go to Spicy Tan Tan and request for NO SHRIMP. Happy to satisfy my craving I prepared the bowl of Ramen upon arrival at home and noted there was close to no ground meat with the broth and there were several dried shrimp. I understand times are tough for all but if one is trying to support their small local establishments paying $18 for noodles and broth is a ripoff.

The noodles were extremely chewy, the eggs were actually cold, first time having them like that. I paid 30 dollars for a lobster and got 1 piece of the claw. The ramen was also SALTY. I wouldn't eat here again

Like.... you walk by this place and think no way is the future food I will dream about forever in there. But damn it. It is. The Spicy Miso Ramen? TO DIE FOR. Edamame? The best I’ve ever had which I didn’t even know was possible. The pork bun? Perfectly balanced with zero fat. I cannot rave about it enough.
Food speaks for itself. Service is the cherry on top. If you have doubts - just visit. You won't find a better spot even if you try. Unless you like watered down flavors 😒

Ramen was average quality, and for the prize 17 onwards it seemed pricey. Additionally our experience was started by a gentleman fixing the door, so imagine eating while the door right next to you is being drilled and the door is opened with 3 C° outside. That justifies the 3 star rating cause the staff was nice.

Very lovely small ramen shop great food tried the shoyu ramen, pork bun and golden lobster app all the dishes were delicious plus awesome service. The lobster with the sweet mayo and cheese was to die for then the ramen broth so salty and savory plus that pork bun the meat was so tender combinated with the sauce in melted in my mouth. Great spot to enjoy some really awesome food.

The ramen soup is super flavorful! It's both a good and bad thing because halfway through, the taste does become a little tiring, but taking a swig of water to reset your palette should do the trick. The restaurant itself could use a little renovating, maybe a paint job. I was a little skeptical with the inspection rating but decided to give it a try anyway. Hopefully they can improve in those aspects.
Lobster Ramen!😍

The 4 stars are for the great service, the amazing broth, and the delicious tori karaage (fried chicken) that is served with japanese mayo. The ramen as a whole isn't that impressive. It's just okay. The portion is plentiful for me. Service is great. All of them are very friendly. They are very accomodating to your need.  It is not hard to find this place. Close enough to the subway station. They also have big sign so people don't have a hard time looking.  Should you give this place a shot? Totally! But, will I come back for the ramen? Nope. Though I will comeback to try their other delicious looking appetizers.

Awesome little gem right by Union x Grand. Sashimi melts in your mouth and I'm a fan of scallions. Pickles are chunky and excellent. Ramen is rich, noods are perfectly firm, and pork just melts in your mouth. Seating is cozy and casual.
Something was not clean

The food was AMAZING and I would definitely go back again but unfortunately I have to give this place three stars because there was a strand of hair in my ramen. Other than that though, the food was 10/10!  Food: I ordered the Ryujin Samurai Ramen and it had that Japanese authenticity which is hard to find in many ramen shops in NYC. The soup was very rich in pork flavor and the noodles were perfect. They weren’t too soft or undercooked. The only downside was that the ramen didn’t come with slices of chashu as other shops usually do. Instead it came with ground pork and chashu has to be added on for two dollars extra. Another dish that stood out to me was the mini chashu bowl. The chashu pieces were very flavorful and you can really taste the smoke in the meat. The size of the bowl also made it perfect for an appetizer.
Great food. Reasonably priced. Gluten free option.

One of my favorite lowkey BK spots. I always go with a group because the tables are pretty big. There's great drink deals. Me and my friends got a huge pitcher of Sapporo! As an app I got the Waygu beef which comes hot and steaming. It's super juicy. The Golden Lobster is super hyped so I was looking forward to showing it off to my friends and they loveddddd it. The lobster is loaded and it's covered in some sort of honey mustard-like sauce which gives it a sweet taste. Will def be back asap.

I used to be a Ryujin diehard. When I got a craving for their tonkotsu shoyu, nothing else in the city could satisfy me, and I'd wait however long it took (more often than not, an hour plus from being seated) to get a bowl. I went back recently and found they'd changed their menu around and the tonkotsu shoyu (among other things) was no longer available. :'( The ramen is still pretty good, but it's not quite as good as the old menu, and I can't justify the long waits. The staff is really lovely though, and the apps are mostly really solid (I absolutely love the torikaraage, the edamame is good, the calamari is just eh and a little too greasy).

I popped in here after getting caught in the rain and their ramen really hit the spot! I got the tan tan (ground pork and beef removed) and the broth was so flavorful and just the right amount of spicy. I also got a pork bun which was also nice (but not as great as Baohaus), but still good. The pork was nice and tender and the sauce drizzled over the bun was a nice touch. They also give you complimentary green tea which was much needed on my cold rainy day visit. Would definitely recommend a visit!
Very comfy spot and the food was very good. Actually best edamame i ever had, they seasoned it with a bit of garlic...yummy! Very good customer service and conversation....Thank You!

They even had cute sushi cocktails 🍣 The location owner is very passionate and cared for every single person in the room. 🙏 I also Highly recommend trying all of their sakes 🙌 Super delicious!

This place is very easy going, but the food is AMAZING! I came here at 2.30 pm on a Sunday and the place was unexpectedly empty, just 2 other couples...both of them were there for the lobster of course!  As I said the place is very basic, not a fancy kind of restaurant, but that didn't matter to us cause the food was really good! We had the Golden Lobster which is basically lobster with grille cheese on top and fries. The dish is worth all the 35$ as you get to eat one full lobster, which is perfectly cooked. We shared the lobster to leave some space for the Teppanyaki Gyoza, best decision ever! These were so good as well!  Too bad this place is quite far for me considering that I live in Weehawken, New Jersey...but I will definitely come back to try their Lobster ramen!

The broth had a ginger type flavor - which was different compared to my other ramen spots. The lobster was extremely fresh and meaty. I also had a side of rice which was very moist and complimented the left over broth. I wish there was an option to order the noodles a different texture. I’m not the biggest al dente fan when it comes to noodle texture. My favorite place to get great, flavorful ramen is Ichiran and this place ramen doesn’t compare. But definitely give it a try.

The food at Ryujin Ramen was amazing!  We’ve tried Fried chicken and Gyoza as appetizers. The Gyoza tasted flavorful and Chicken was very crispy. The waiter recommended their most popular Ramen.  One was TanTan Men and the other was Shiro Ramen with cheese. The TanTan Men has black sesame flavored spicy noodle soup topped with ground pork TanTan sauce mixed with minced shiitake mushroom and bamboo,green onion on top.  The Shiro ramen has Pork based noodle soup, BBQ pork, Steamed cabbage, black mushroom. And I added cheese on the top. It  tasted creamy with the soup.  They all were delicious. We were so addicted to the Ramen. I would love to bring my friends to this restaurant for them to experience the wonderful flavors of Ramen.
